deck: "Join New York's prettiest detective, Jennifer Mays, and true crime writer Gabriel Webb, in another fair-play whodunit that challenges you to solve the mystery as it unfolds!"
description:
In "Magic & Monsters And Murder," Jennifer and Gabe enter the world of dungeons and dragons, and death when a player of a popular role-playing game is found murdered -- just hours after his character was killed!

*This issue carries no editor credit, however it can logically be assumed that the edits were done by regular series editor David Campiti.
name: Magic and Monsters-and Murder
The Unguarded Hour

deck: "Join New York's prettiest detective, Jennifer Mays, and true crime writer Gabriel Webb, in another fair-play whodunit that challenges you to solve the mystery as it unfolds!"
description:
Jen and Gabe visit a Biosphere called Eden II, an artificial environment constructed in the Southwest. Its director of marine ecological systems has been murdered and Eden II's patron needs The MAZE Agency to solve the crime!

*This issue was written as an intentional homage for the anniversary of Edgar Allen Poe's "Murders in the Rue Morgue", which is widely considered to be the first detective story.
name: Crime in Eden

description: The War of The Marvels is over, but before Carol Danvers can deal with its aftermath, she must brace herself as she faces down the biggest mistake she made before her apparent death, promising Spider-Man she'd go out with him! Then, Ms. Marvel vs. Mystique! She raised Rogue, the woman who stole Carol's powers and memories, and now the sinister shape-shifter is coming for Ms. Marvel herself! Collecting MS. MARVEL #47-50.
name: Volume 9

volume.name: Ms. Marvel: Best You Can Be

name: Murder Mission
Brink Of Danger
The Shield Of Auray

description: In a Victorian-era tale of magic and romance, young Tristran Thorn falls in love with the town beauty and must go on an incredible coming-of-age journey in order to capture her heart. Living in the small countryside town of Wall, one night Tristran vows to his beloved to retrieve a fallen star that they witnessed crashing down from the heavens. Now to gain his love's hand, he must leave behind his home and embark on a journey that will define the meaning of true love. Told through breathtaking painted illustrations, this fairytale for adults is a true masterpiece in storytelling.
name: Oversized HC/TPB

volume.name: Neil Gaiman and Charles Vess' Stardust

description: Collected for the first time, this tale stars Edwin and Charles from THE SANDMAN: SEASON OF MISTS. Their first case involves a string of grisly murders and the immortal Hob Gadling. Written by Ed Brubaker (Captain America, SLEEPER).
name: TPB

volume.name: The Sandman Presents: The Dead Boy Detectives

description: The world's oldest, most powerful witch returns in this collection written by Bill Willingham (FABLES). This tale follows Thessaly as she becomes the unwitting partner in a monster-killing business with her ghostly one-time nemesis, Fetch.
name: TPB

volume.name: The Sandman Presents: Thessaly: Witch for Hire

description:
In this fast-paced, gritty murder mystery, Jack Herriman, a young private detective burdened with a checkered past, looks to begin his rebirth by taking on a simple missing persons case. But when the woman he is searching for turns up dead, the flawed detective delves into her family's past and uncovers a Pandora's box of dark secrets. Now struggling with the reemergence of his own issues of guilt and rage, Jack must navigate through a labyrinth of adultery, betrayal, and vengeance to piece together the buried truth of the past and discover the real identity of the killer.

Back Blurb

Jack Herriman isn't the kind of guy to run away from a tough case, but the death of a young woman he was hired to find will test his limits. What starts as a simple missing persons case will lead him to down a cooked path of sex drugs and murder where the only thing more elusive than the killer is the truth, hiding among the emotional wreckage of the past.

Written by Ed Brubaker (DEADENDERS, An Accidental Death), with pencils by Michael Lark (TERMINAL CITY, Raymond Chandler's The Little Sister) and inks by Sean Phillips (THE INVISIBLES, HELL ETERNAL), SCENE OF THE CRIME is a realistic, modern take on the classic hard-boiled detective story in the spirit of Raymond Chandler and Ross Macdonald, served up in the inimitable VERTIGO style.
name: TPB

volume.name: Scene of the Crime: A Little Piece of Goodnight

deck: "Join New York's prettiest detective, Jennifer Mays, and true crime writer Gabriel Webb, in another fair-play whodunit that challenges you to solve the mystery as it unfolds!"
description:
In "Valentine's Slay," the boyfriend of Jennifer Mays' secretary Sandy is assaulted with a bow and arrow.

Is it the work of "The Cupid," who is terrorizing gays in Greenwich Village? Or is it the work of a copycat killer?
name: Valentine's Slay

description: A new collection featuring issues #15-20 of the ongoing series. With the consciousness of Alec Holland still separated from its former host and scattered across the world, the Swamp Thing must face a new threat to the Green which is manifesting itself inside a growing dead zone in the Gulf of Mexico.
name: Vol. 3

description: With dynamic painted art by Alex Ross (KINGDOM COME, SUPERMAN: PEACE ON EARTH), UNCLE SAM is the story of a star-spangled vagrant guided by the voices in his head and his own fractured memories. Absorbed by history-travelling visions of America's dark past, Uncle Sam struggles to piece together the scattered clues of his own experiences in this deep and thoughtful look at America's checkered past.
name: TPB

description: From the fertile mind and nimble fingers of writer Grant Morrison and artist Philip Bond comes the latest in multiculturalist spectacle! Color, song and cosmic violence collide in VIMANARAMA, collecting the 3-issue Vertigo miniseries that fuses East and West together into a transcendental delight of romance and danger. Feel the Earth tremble as 19-year-old grocer's son Ali and his beautiful arranged bride Sofia accidentally unleash an ancient race of unimaginable evil from beneath Bradford, England, then summon the equally powerful Prince Ben Rama and his Ultrahadeen to do battle against them. Shudder as Ben Rama reveals his love for Sofia, the reincarnation of his immortal soul mate, only to lose all his power at her hesitation. And thrill to the final battle between good and evil, played out over the ancient land of Atlantis together with the consummation of the ultimate end-of-the-world love story. All this and more awaits you in VIMANARAMA, the best of all worlds!
name: TPB

description: Collecting the first four 56-page one-shots from writer Garth Ennis' acclaimed WAR STORY run at VERTIGO, this 240-page collection features some of the finest war comics ever to see print in the modern age. A labor of love by Ennis (PREACHER, HELLBLAZER, HITMAN, The Punisher), WAR STORIES VOL. 1 tells four very different stories from four of the countless viewpoints on World War II. WAR STORIES VOL. 1 also includes a new afterword by Ennis.
name: Vol. 1

description: Reprinting the second quartet of WAR STORY one-shots from acclaimed writer Garth Ennis. This collection showcases tales of a world at war from the North African desert, the skies over Germany, the battlefields of Spain and the waters of the North Atlantic, with a new afterword by Ennis.
name: Vol. 2

description:
On the first day of high school, Kyon's boring life takes an abrupt turn as he gets pulled into Haruhi's plan to start a school club.

Back Blurb

It's average schoolboy Kyon's typical first day at an ordinary high school. Little does he know that his humdrum life is about to get a dose of the superfantastic thanks to fellow classmate Haruhi Suzumiya!

Are you ready to join the SOS Brigade?!

Chapters 1 through 5.
name: Vol. 1

description: It's the evolution of Ms. Marvel as the mantle passes from one heroine to the next! Carol Danvers has fought for years as Ms. Marvel, taking her inspiration and name from the Kree hero Mar-Vell, known to most of Earth as Captain Marvel. But with the former super villain Norman Osborn rising to power and taking control of the Avengers, Danvers is forbidden not only from wearing her costume but from even using the name Ms. Marvel. Complicating matters further, her powers have become unreliable and now cause her excruciating pain. Can she fight through the hurt to track down her old foe, Ghazi Rashid? Meanwhile, the devious Osborn has taken steps to replace Danvers, turning to none other than Dr. Karla Sofen - better known as the super villain-turn-Thunderbolt Moonstone! Collecting MS. MARVEL #35-41.
name: Volume 7

description:
In the days following the Secret Invasion, there is a death in the family. Brian Reed (SECRET INVASION: SPIDER-MAN) and Marcos Marz (Batman) begin the tale of Ms. Marvel's new life post-Secret Invasion. Then, it's Marvel Pirate Mania as the Storyteller returns! Gavin is a young man with the ability to reshape the world in his image, but when he crosses paths with Ms. Marvel once more, dark secrets are revealed, and Gavin's life takes a dark turn. Plus: it's a Brand New Day as Ms. Marvel and the Amazing Spider-Man cross paths. Can they settle their own differences and save Manhattan from menacing mechanized malcontents?

Collecting MS. MARVEL #31-34, MS. MARVEL SPECIAL: STORYTELLER and MS. MARVEL ANNUAL #1.
name: Volume 6

description: A MAGIC EVENT that spans across the ages, featuring the craftiest characters and most spellbinding stories in the Marvel Universe! In the vein of the wild and woolly genre revitalization Annihilation, Marvel's looking into its crystal ball to bring you mystical mages, scandalous sorcerers and fantastic flights of high-flying fantasy in MYSTIC ARCANA. Each of the primary stories revolves around the introduction of one of a select group of mystical implements, quite literally the four pillars of the universe and the involvement of a character from Marvel's rich, magical past - including Magik, the Black Knight, Sister Grimm and the Scarlet Witch. Plus: Witness the efforts of Dr. Strange adversary, sorcerer Ian McNee, to collect arcane implements in a series of shorter companion tales that make up the spine of MYSTIC ARCANA. Collecting MYSTIC ARCANA: MAGIK, BLACK KNIGHT, SCARLET WITCH, SISTER GRIMM; and THE OFFICIAL TAROT OF THE MARVEL UNIVERSE.
name: HC

description: Aided by his closest allies, Ray Palmer, the Amazing Atom, embarks on a desperate quest through unknown universes to find the love of his life - Jean Loring!
name: The Other Side of Doomsday!; The Eternity Pursuit!

description: The new miniseries by fantasy writer Tad Williams heats up! The Iron Ring has sent the emissary called Sion to bring the Next back to their home for judgment and sentencing...but they can't go back without killing Monikka! And even Superman has a tough time going up against Sion...
name: Just Killing Time, Part Two: Swearing at George Washington

description: Superman is trapped in a time anomaly. Can even the Next - super-powered beings who can change the world in their wake - rescue the Man of Steel? Will Superman's power be enough against Sion, the killer sent from the Next's home dimension to kill them?
name: Just Killing Time, Part Three: Truth, Justice and the Carbon-Based Way

description: The fist of the Iron Ring, the otherdimensional enforcer known as Sion, threatens the new superhero team The Next - and if they're threatened, Monikka's life hangs in the balance! Only Superman is strong enough to go mano a mano with Sion - but is even his power enough?
name: Just Killing Time, Part Four: When Elephants Dance

description: A showdown between Superman and Sion! Metron warns that the entire Metaverse is threatened! Monikka Wong and her other-dimensional companions are caught between the Fist of the Iron Ring and the end of everything!
name: Just Killing Time, Part Five: Falling Sideways

description: The incredible miniseries conclusion! It's 'Monika Wong vs. the End of Everything,' or Superman, the Next and Metron vs. the Oblivion Shadow, the most unimaginable threat to ever threaten our world!
name: Just Killing Time, Part Six: Monika Wong vs. The End of Everything

description: Part 2 of "Freddy Krueger's A Nightmare On Elm Street"
name: Dreamstlker, Part 2

volume.name: Freddy Krueger's A Nightmare on Elm Street

name: The Escapist / The Starstruck / The Betrayed

description: These are the cartoon strip (mis)adventures of Britain's first and best loved World War II Pin-up -- the scintillating, blue eyed, blond-haired, clothes-phobic cartoon legend that is Lady Jane Gay. The ever patriotic Jane wasted no time in joining up after Britain's entry into the war following a brief stint as a chauffeur, secretary and with the W.A.A.F.S. Jane finally joined Army Intelligence in 1941 where she stayed off and on for the remainder of the war, battling 5th columnists and Nazi spies. The strip originally appeared in the Daily Mirror in 1932 and ran to 1959 and she was at her most famous and inspirational during the war years...
name: The Misadventures Of Jane

description: A few days after meeting Manami, a new friend Ayumu made on her first day of high school, Manami attempts suicide because of a breakup with her boyfriend, Katsumi. Ayumu saves her from death, but Manami will need more support from those around her. Ayumu decides to visit Katsumi at his home, where she finds something shocking about him.
name: Vol. 2

description: Get ready for the most extensive journey ever into the brilliant mind of Graham Annable! A classically trained animator with credits in film (including as a storyboard artist on Coraline), television, and video games, Annable has for years spent his free time creating some of the funniest, most poignant comics anywhere. As befits his animation background, Annable's fluid art pulses with life, in stories that practically jump off the page. Alternately poetic and hilarious, Grickle presents a strange twist on the everyday with heart and humor. If you've experienced Grickle before, this is the greatest collection yet. If you haven't, there's no better introduction than Book of Grickle! o Grickle was named one of Wizard's Top 25 indie books everyone must read! The best of Grickle, plus new and rarely seen material! o Graham Annables's Grickle strips were selected for Houghton-Mifflin's 2008 edition of Best American Comics.

Ayumu's depression worsens as a shock from the aftermath of her tryst with Katsumi. To calm down, she walks to a lake where she finds Miki Hatori and then confides to her. This results in a confidence boost that later turns into rage as she watches Miki being bullied by Manami and her clique.
name: Vol. 3

description: Things are growing ultimately wrong as Ayumu gets cornered in her own room by Katsumi. She'll need a miracle in order to escape. She also needs one for the impending bullying that Manami's Clique will force upon her for standing up for Miki.
name: Vol. 4

description: Ayumu has many decisions to make as the jaws of death approach her due to a full scale assault by the whole of Niishidate High. Just like the past issues, she relies on cutting herself to ease her pain, but even that will not be enough to save her "life" from inpending "death", unless she deals with the situation another way.
name: Vol. 5

description: The movie tie-in edition of the best selling series from Millar and Romita JR.
name: Kick-Ass

name: The Woman from Aladdin: Part One
The Woman From Aladdin: Part Two

description: During the 1950s, Hellboy caravans across Mexico with a trio of vampire-killing luchadores, finding the undead; evil turkeys; a terrible bat god; and a little too much tequila. Reuniting Mike Mignola and Richard Corben, the creative team behind the Eisner Award-winning miniseries Hellboy: The Crooked Man!
name: Hellboy In Mexico or, A Drunken Blur

first_appearance_teams.name: Bureau for Paranormal Research and Defense

team_credits.name: Bureau for Paranormal Research and Defense

description:
Major Gunther Stolle of the SS did not believe in ghosts a brutal thug like him didnt bother with such nonsense. Even when tough German troops broke and fled, gasping out tales of a phantom tank crew, he still didnt believe it.
But soon he was going to know the terrible truth, for the commander of the tank had vowed to hunt him downeven from beyond the grave!
name: Revenge of the Phantom

description: Thanks to his time machine malfunctioning, every door and electronic device in Dilton's house becomes a portal to another era. Dilton and Danni have to resolve the situation before they or a near-sighted elderly relative get gurt by the less-than-friendly visitors (pirates, World War II combatants, etc)
